Core ConceptUsers right-click (or use a hotkey) on a price level, trendline, or indicator setup on any FeatureChart → "Forge Trade Idea." The system then builds a live, updating probabilistic simulation of that potential entry, combining:Your existing tools (VRVP/POC, SMMA regime, drawdown, ATR, macro regime quadrant, correlations, etc.) as foundational inputs.
Forward Monte Carlo-style path simulations (hundreds/thousands of paths) conditioned on current microstructure, volatility, and macro.
A proprietary Narrative Resonance Score (0-100) that quantifies alignment between price behavior and real-time fundamental/macro/news drivers.

The output is a visual "Confidence Forge" overlay/pane that gives users an at-a-glance probability distribution for outcomes (e.g., "Probability of +8% in 10 sessions: 62% ± confidence interval"), risk/reward asymmetry, and a clear "Resonance" gauge showing whether the move is "supported by the story" or fighting it.How It Works (User Flow & Implementation Fit)Trigger & Setup:User defines a simple idea: Long AAPL at $220 (near POC), target $240, stop $210; or "breakout above SMMA ribbon."
Optional: Add custom assumptions (e.g., "assuming no recession signal spike").

The Forge Engine (Rust compute module, like your Analysis tabs):Pulls live/historical data from your charts + macro tabs (Regime Quadrant, Recession Prob, NFCI, Yield Curve spreads, correlations).
Runs fast simulations (vectorized, perhaps using existing libs or simple stochastic models like GBM with regime jumps, volatility clustering from ATR, volume-weighted paths from VRVP).
Incorporates drawdown history to model realistic recovery paths.
Narrative Resonance Layer (the truly novel part): Cross-references recent news flow, earnings sentiment, macro releases, sector correlations, and regime (e.g., "Goldilocks" vs. "Stagflation"). It scores how well the proposed price path matches historical analogs where narrative and price aligned (or diverged). Use simple NLP on headlines or structured macro events if you have feeds; otherwise, proxy via volatility regimes and cross-asset moves.

Visual Output (seamless with your charting):Probability Fan/Envelope overlaid on the chart (semi-transparent cones showing median path + 25/75/90% bands, color-coded by regime from SMMA).
Conviction Meter: Single 0-100 score with breakdown (e.g., 78% — "Strong: High volume support at entry (VRVP), bull regime, macro tailwind, resonance 92").
Outcome Histogram: Side pane showing % probability of hitting target before stop, expected value, max simulated drawdown.
Resonance Callout: "High resonance: Price respecting POC aligns with easing financial conditions and positive sector rotation (RRG)." Or warning: "Low resonance — fighting broader yield curve steepening."
Live updating as new bars print or macro data lands. Toggle like other indicators.
Linked cursor: Hover in Forge view updates other charts.

Advanced/Scanner Integration:Scanner column: "Forge Conviction" for watchlist tickers (pre-compute common setups like "near POC" or "regime flip").
Pairs/RRG tab extension: Forge relative trades.
Export PNG includes the Forge summary for journaling.

